Very good food for a very low price! The staff is very nice and might even undercharge you if you come in close to closing time when they are trying to unload the last of their food. Great if you want a seafood option but honestly La Isla Cuchifritos Restaurant (about three streets down on graham ave, closer to flushing ave) is slightly better. Might just be because of their beef or plantain stuffed mashed potato fried balls!

You wouldn't know it by looking at it but this place has great food. It's very Spanish too. Definitely a casual place to go for a good heavy meal. Plates are stacked up with food and its a sit where ever you want kind of deal. Some nights the owner invites a band to play music.I wish I could give this place that last star but unfortunately the waitresses could be better. Ours wasn't rude or anything but she wasn't 100% helpful when we asked her was some of the dishes were. Other than that a great place for some real Spanish food!
